-- European shares halt sell-off; Orange rallies on EE talks
-- By Blaise Robinson
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 03:14AM EST
-- None



PARIS, Dec 16 (Reuters) - European shares inched up in early trading on Tuesday, halting their week-long sell-off, with Orange <ORAN.PA> and Deutsche Telekom <DTEGn.DE> rallying on news of talks with BT <BT.L> to sell EE.

Orange was up 4.1 percent and Deutsche Telekom up 1.4 percent after the two firms entered exclusive talks with BT for a potential 12.5 billion-pound ($19.6 billion) sale of EE. [ID:nL6N0TZ3IU]